	<h1>Water Conservation Facts</h1>

	<article id="depletion">

		<h2>Water Depletion</h2>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-12">
				<p>Water conservation is extremely crucial for the wellbeing of the Earth and all its inhabitants. Recently, we have been depleting more water than can be replaced naturally over decade-long periods. Our current aquifers have been declining at alarming rates, and our source of water will only continue to drop as population and our reliance on these aquifers grow. The consequences are critical, and these are all the more reasons to conserve water!</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">

			<div class="col-sm-4">
				<%= image_tag("info/bottle") %>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-8">

				<p>More Information:</p>

				<ul>
					<li><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2015/06/16/new-nasa-studies-show-how-the-world-is-running-out-of-water/" target="_blank">Washington Post</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://water.usgs.gov/edu/gwdepletion.html" target="_blank">United States Geological Survey</a></li>
				</ul>

			</div>

		</div>

	</article>

	<article id="ice-caps">

		<h2>Freshwater in Ice Caps</h2>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-12">
				<p>Although the Earth consists mainly of water, only 3% of all of Earth's water is freshwater. Among the 3%, just 1% of our freshwater is easily accessible, with much of it trapped in glaciers and snowfields. In essence, only 0.007% of the planet's water is available to fuel and feed its 7.4 billion people. However, the glaciers contain 68.7% of all of Earthâ€™s freshwater, and provide hope for a large supplement of clean drinkable water!</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">

			<div class="col-sm-4">
				<%= image_tag("info/ice") %>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-8">

				<p>More Information:</p>

				<ul>
					<li><a href="http://water.usgs.gov/edu/watercycleice.html" target="_blank">United States Geological Survey</a></li>
				</ul>

			</div>

		</div>

	</article>

	<article id="groundwater">

		<h2>Inaccessible Groundwater</h2>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-12">
				<p>The second largest source of freshwater is right under our noses. 30.1% of freshwater is groundwater. However, only 45% of groundwater is accessible. The other 55% is too far underground for us to be able to reach it right now. Since the Earth is extremely limited in freshwater, we all have to pitch in to make a difference!</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">

			<div class="col-sm-4">
