		</div>

	</article>

	<article id="sahara">

		<h2>Sub-Saharan Africa Water Usage</h2>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-12">
				<p>Sub-Saharan Africa is living proof that humans can live with 90% or more reduction to our water, and that we should use water much more sparingly. Sub-Saharan Africa is located just south of the Sahara Desert in Africa. The residents of this location only use 2-5 gallons daily while the average American uses roughly 100. We should strive to have as small of a water footprint as possible.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

